1. Introduction

In the Homework 2 of IE360: Statistical Forecasting and Time Series course, the ultimate task is to forecast the sales of UGS for every quarter of 2007 by using time series regression methods.

Here are the first and last six rows of the data:

2. Time Series Plot of UGS

In the time series plot of UGS, there is a decreasing trend and an obvious seasonality for every year. In addition, the time series does not have stationary mean and variance. KPSS test is used to check the stationarity of the series. Since the test statistic is higher than critical values, the time series is not stationary.

## 
## ####################### 
## # KPSS Unit Root Test # 
## ####################### 
## 
## Test is of type: mu with 2 lags. 
## 
## Value of test-statistic is: 0.8149 
## 
## Critical value for a significance level of: 
##                 10pct  5pct 2.5pct  1pct
## critical values 0.347 0.463  0.574 0.739

4. Model Selection

4.1. Alternative Model I

In correlation plots of UGS, there can be seen a significant correlation between UGS and other parameters NLPG, NUGV, GNPA. That is the reason why the regression modeling will start with those as predictors.

4.4. Alternative Model IV

UGSs logarithm is taken to linearize it and used as target variable in the models. Likewise, variables with nonlinear increase can be included in the models as a predictor by taking the logarithm. In addition, data number 6, 12 and 28 are outliers and they are removed from the model. This is the best model because Residual standard error and p-value are close to 0, Adjusted R-squared is close to 1. Alternative Model IV will be used in forecasting of UGS in 2007.

## 
## Call:
## lm(formula = log(UGS) ~ log(NLPG) + trend + season2 + season3 + 
##     season4, data = data[(1:28) != 6 & (1:28) != 12 & (1:28) != 
##     28, ])
##

5. Model Validation

## 
##  Breusch-Godfrey test for serial correlation of order up to 9
## 
## data:  Residuals
## LM test = 14.025, df = 9, p-value = 0.1214

In residual analysis it can be seen that residuals are not autocorrelated and distributed normally. Also residuals scatter around mean zero and seem to have a constant variance. Thus this model satisfies the assumptions and it is good enough to use for the prediction of the next years quarterly sales.
